FT  19 JUN 92 / Tax-free letting scheme announced
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE government yesterday announced a 'rent-a-room' scheme to encourage
householders to let out rooms.
The scheme, promised in the Conservative election manifesto, allows rental
payments of up to Pounds 3,250 a year to be free of tax.
Up to Pounds 62.50 a week of gross rent paid on furnished lettings in the
taxpayer's only or main home will be tax-free. If the gross income exceeds
Pounds 3,250, the taxpayer can choose to pay tax on the excess (with no
allowance for expenses) or to pay tax on the whole profit after deduction of
expenses. The tax relief comes into effect this financial year.
