<TEXT>
A Russian Sukhoi Su 27 fighter, which Nato has codenamed Flanker, was put
through its paces above London's Thames Barrier yesterday, Daniel Green
writes.
It is one of the most advanced fighters built in the former Soviet Union.
The aircraft is equipped to carry up to 10 air-to-air guided missiles and is
also designed as an escort for long-range bombers. The potency of the
Flanker prompted European countries to embark on the troubled European
Fighter Aircraft project. Sponsored by a Russian insurance company, this
particular Flanker is visiting Britain for the Biggin Hill air show, where
it is part of a newly established Russian aerobatics team called The Test
Pilots.
