FT  19 JUN 92 / Observer: Abstract verb
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Why is it that most of us would 'extract' water but the National Rivers
Authority warns about excessive 'abstraction'?
Of the industry's several contradictory explanations, the one that makes the
most sense is that 'extraction' is permanent while 'abstraction' implies
that the water eventually will be returned to the river.
Observer suspects that, unlike the hapless River Darent, this one may run
and run.
