FT  19 JUN 92 / Technology (Worth Watching): Spreadsheet keeps itself in
check
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ONE of the chores of building a computer spreadsheet is checking that the
data has been accurately entered. Reading the numbers back to a colleague is
both time-consuming and tedious.
But Temair Software, based in Rhode Island, has developed a software package
called Spreadsheet Echo which enables the computer to read Lotus 1-2-3
spreadsheet numbers back to the user.
The software will read back a range of numbers either by row or column, can
be told to pause between cells, and speak in either a male or female voice.
The user can also set speed or volume levels and listen through the
computer's internal speaker or through headphones.
The programme, which costs Dollars 99.95, is also multilingual.
