FT  19 JUN 92 / International Company News: Enso-Gutzeit FM76m in the red in
spite of sales gain
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   STOCKHOLM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ENSO-Gutzeit, the Finnish pulp and paper group, has returned a FM76m loss
(after financial items) for the first four months of the year, compared with
a FM182m (Dollars 42.4m) loss for the same period of 1991, writes Robert
Taylor in Stockholm.
Net sales went up by 9.3 per cent to FM3.36bn. The company said internal
rationalisation measures would ensure a continuing revival towards
profitability, but operations would still be showing a loss by the end of
the year.
Mr Jukka Harmala said competition had kept prices down, particularly for
fine papers and publication papers, while the paperboard market was stable
and demand for Scandinavian sawn timber increased.
