FT  18 JUN 92 / Cohse to drop opposition to trusts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CATHERINE MILTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE health service union Cohse looks likely to drop its campaign against
self-governing hospital trusts, Catherine Milton writes.
The move would mean the 200,000-strong union, which represents about 20 per
cent of health service staff, accepting the end of centralised collective
bargaining in the NHS and concentrating on local deals. It would remain
opposed to the principle of trusts.
NHS bargaining has traditionally been highly centralised, but the spread of
trusts has led to fragmentation. The union believes that centralised
bargaining will remain important for setting national minimum rates.
Discussions will take place at regional and branch level in the next few
weeks.
