FT  18 JUN 92 / World Stock Markets: Sao Paulo shares tumble
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sao Paulo shares fell another 8.9 per cent as investors sold heavily amid
growing concern over new charges of corruption in the government, brokers
said. The Bovespa index ended at 19,964, down 1,901.
In Mexico, the stock exchange took its second worst fall ever, closing down
99.65, or 5.89 per cent, at 1,593.3 after touching 1,526.9.
Heavy selling set prices on a free fall amid fears of a delay or block in
the free trade agreement and continued uncertainty over the status of
Telefonos de Mexico shares owned by telephone workers.
